{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"55e66653-12fa-49ee-b7c1-339026f4ff6f","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 (4.x) dropped support for .NET 6.0 — it requires **net8.0** or later.\n\nYour project targets `net6.0`, and .NET 6 itself is already **out of support** (ended Nov 2024).\n\n### Options\n\n1. **Upgrade your target framework** to `net8.0` (or `net9.0`), then upgrade MSTest to v4.\n2. **Stay on MSTest 3.x** if you must remain on `net6.0`.\n\nYour test code (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert`) is simple and won't need API changes for MSTest v4 — the only blocker is the TFM.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"84730690-4980-4b5a-9481-cc4461091946","outputTokens":182},"id":"1e7e478c-f271-4b3d-8d87-a2a5ae7ad61a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:20:01.386Z","parentId":"9d4fe9fe-b686-46a9-911b-666d23f0027b"}
